 created cinematic works of art that are also deeply philosophical. His contribution to philosophy through a half century of filmmaking has become the focus of increasing scholarly attention. Inviting the reader along a journey of reflections at the intersection of film, art, and philosophy, Life Above the Clouds brings together an international team of contributors to present the most current and definitive statement of the filmmaker's work. Accessibly written and exploring films such as Badlands, Days of Heaven, The Thin Red Line, The New World, The Tree of Life, To the Wonder, Knight of Cups, Song to Song, and A Hidden Life, the nineteen essays herein will be of interest not only to scholars and students of philosophy, theology, film studies, and aesthetics, but also to anyone with a true love of film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPhilosophy in motion pictures. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Aesthetics. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBackman, Jussi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraver, Lee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCerbone, David R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraig, Candace R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeLay, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeLay, Steven, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFisher, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGutschmidt, Rico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4ht